cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper is about a distributed algorithm for learning personalized models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the algorithm is designed to be implementation-friendly and asynchronous, which suggests that it may be relevant to the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions that the algorithm requires the personal loss functions to be strongly convex and have Lipschitz gradient, which are properties that are often studied in the context of optimization, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to the category of cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper's focus on learning personalized models suggests that it may also be relevant to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
